Integrate and Fire Model#

Introduction#

Integrate and Fire neuron, also known as perfect integrate-and-fire model and non-leaky integrate-and-fire, is one of the earliest neuron models.

The neuronal dynamics equation for the integrate and fire neurons is:

\[\frac{dV(t)}{dt} = \frac{I(t)}{C}\]

where:

\(V(t)\) is the membrane voltage

\(I(t)\) is the injected current

\(C\) is the membrane capacitance

When there is a current input, the membrane voltage increases until it reaches a constant threshold \(V_{th}\), at which point a delta function peaks and resets the voltage to the resting potential \(V_{rest}\), and the model continues to run.

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from bokeh.io import output_notebook
from bokeh.layouts import row, column
from bokeh.plotting import show, figure
from bokeh.models import ColumnDataSource, Slider, CustomJS

output_notebook()
Loading BokehJS ... 
V_init=-80

params=dict(V_T=[-50.0], V_0=[-80], V_imp=[-20],
            C=[1], dt=[1e-5],
            )

params_source = ColumnDataSource(data=params)

def iaf_step(I_ext, V, dt, params=params):
    dt = dt * 1000
    V_T = params['V_T'][0]
    V_0 = params['V_0'][0]
    V_imp = params['V_imp'][0]
    C = params['C'][0]
    
    V1 = V + dt * (I_ext/C)
    if V1 >= V_T:
        if V1 >= V_imp:
            V1 = V_0
        else:
            V1 = V_imp

    return V1

dt = 1e-5
t = np.arange(0, 1, dt)

I_ext = np.zeros_like(t)
I_ext[int(0.2*len(t)):int(0.8*len(t))] = 1

V = np.zeros_like(t)
N = np.zeros_like(t)
V[0] = V_init

for i in range(len(t)):
    V_pre = iaf_step(I_ext[i], V[i], dt)
    if i < len(t)-1:
        V[i+1] = V_pre

source = ColumnDataSource(data=dict(I=I_ext, V=V, t=t))

callback_V_T = CustomJS(args=dict(source=source, params_source=params_source), code="""
    let data = source.data;

    let t = data['t']
    let I = data['I']
    let dt = params_source.data['dt'][0]
    let V = Array(t.length).fill(0)

    
    V[0] = data['V'][0]

    let iaf_step = function(I_ext, V, dt, params_source){
        dt = dt*1e3
        let V_T = cb_obj.value
        
        let V_0 = params_source.data['V_0'][0]
        let V_imp = params_source.data['V_imp'][0]
        let C   = params_source.data['C'][0]
        
        let V1 = V + dt * (I_ext/C)
        if (V1 >= V_T){
            if (V1 >= V_imp){
                V1 = V_0
            }
            else{
                V1 = V_imp
            }
        }
        
        return [V1, V_T]
    }
    
    let V_T = 0;
    for (let i=0; i<t.length;i++){
        let pre = iaf_step(I[i], V[i], dt, params_source)
        let V_pre = pre[0]
        V_T = pre[1]
        if (i < t.length-1){
            V[i+1] = V_pre
        }
    }
    
    params_source.data['V_T'][0] = V_T;
    source.data['V'] = V;
    
    source.change.emit();
    params_source.change.emit();
    
""")

callback_C = CustomJS(args=dict(source=source, params_source=params_source), code="""
    let data = source.data;

    let t = data['t']
    let I = data['I']
    let dt = params_source.data['dt'][0]
    let V = Array(t.length).fill(0)

    
    V[0] = data['V'][0]

    let iaf_step = function(I_ext, V, dt, params_source){
        dt = dt*1e3
        let C = cb_obj.value
        
        let V_0 = params_source.data['V_0'][0]
        let V_T = params_source.data['V_T'][0]
        let V_imp = params_source.data['V_imp'][0]
        
        let V1 = V + dt * (I_ext/C)
        if (V1 >= V_T){
            if (V1 >= V_imp){
                V1 = V_0
            }
            else{
                V1 = V_imp
            }
        }
        
        return [V1, C]
    }
    
    let C = 0;
    for (let i=0; i<t.length;i++){
        let pre = iaf_step(I[i], V[i], dt, params_source)
        let V_pre = pre[0]
        C = pre[1]
        if (i < t.length-1){
            V[i+1] = V_pre
        }
    }
    
    params_source.data['C'][0] = C;
    source.data['V'] = V;
    
    source.change.emit();
    params_source.change.emit();
    
""")

p1 = figure(width=600, height=300, title='I')
p1.line('t', 'I', source=source, line_color='orange', line_width=3)
p1.background_fill_color = "gainsboro"

p2 = figure(width=600, height=300, title='V')
p2.line('t', 'V', source=source, line_color='skyblue', line_width=3)
p2.background_fill_color = "gainsboro"

slider_V_T = Slider(start=-70.0, end=0.0, value=-50.0, step=1.0, title="V_T")
slider_V_0 = Slider(start=-90.0, end=0.0, value=-80.0, step=1.0, title="V_0")
slider_V_imp = Slider(start=-70.0, end=0.0, value=-20.0, step=1.0, title="V_imp")
slider_C = Slider(start=0.0, end=10.0, value=1.0, step=.1, title="C")

slider_V_T.js_on_change('value_throttled', callback_V_T)
slider_V_0.js_on_change('value_throttled', callback_V_0)
slider_V_imp.js_on_change('value_throttled', callback_V_imp)
slider_C.js_on_change('value_throttled', callback_C)

inputs = column(slider_V_T, slider_V_0, slider_V_imp, slider_C)

plots = column(p1, p2)

layout = row(inputs, plots)

show(layout)
